-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/bnp-paribas-to-buy-securities-unit-of-south-africa-s-cadiz-les-echos-says.html
BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA plans to buy 60
percent of the brokerage unit of  Cadiz Holdings Ltd. (CDZ) , Les Echos
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The stake BNP is buying is worth about 10 million euros,
the Paris-based newspaper said. Cadiz Chief Executive Officer
Ram Barkai will respond to requests for comment at about 9 a.m.
Johannesburg time, Sonia Jamoulle, a spokeswoman for Cape Town-
based Cadiz, said in a text message today.  Cadiz on June 30 said it is in talks with an international
bank about a potential transaction involving its securities
business, without giving more detail.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  